'''Charles Marc S. De Ketelaere''' ({{IPA|nl|də ˈkeːtəˌlaːrə}}; born 10 March 2001) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Italian football updater|Atalanta}} club [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Club career==
=== Club Brugge ===
De Ketelaere joined [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] at the age of seven, also working as a ball boy.<ref name="auto">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58916176|title=Is De Ketelaere Belgium's new De Bruyne?|publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=19 October 2021|archive-date=19 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019113518/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58916176|url-status=live}}</ref> He also played tennis as a youth, but chose to pursue football.<ref name="auto"/>

He made his senior debut on 25 September 2019, when he played the full game in the [[2019–20 Belgian Cup]] matchup against [[Francs Borains]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/25/belgium/beker-van-belgie/boussu-dour-borinage/club-brugge-kv/3155220/|title=Francs Borains v Club Brugge game report|date=25 September 2019|access-date=30 October 2019|archive-date=30 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030032427/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/25/belgium/beker-van-belgie/boussu-dour-borinage/club-brugge-kv/3155220/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 22 October 2019, he made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut against [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]. He started the game and was substituted in the 57th minute with the score of 1–0 to Paris Saint-Germain, the game eventually ended with a 5–0 loss.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/10/22/europe/uefa-champions-league/club-brugge-kv/paris-saint-germain-fc/3160563/|title=Club Brugge v PSG game report|date=22 October 2019|access-date=30 October 2019|archive-date=29 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429163742/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/10/22/europe/uefa-champions-league/club-brugge-kv/paris-saint-germain-fc/3160563/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 February 2020, he scored a goal in a 2–1 win against [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] to reach the [[2020 Belgian Cup final|Belgian Cup final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2019-2020/halve-finale/02/club-staat-in-de-bekerfinale-met-dank-aan-gouden-invaller-de-ketelaere~1566819483069/ |title=Club staat in de bekerfinale met dank aan gouden invaller De Ketelaere |website=sporza.be |language=Dutch |date=5 February 2020 |access-date=20 October 2020 |archive-date=22 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022160540/https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2019-2020/halve-finale/02/club-staat-in-de-bekerfinale-met-dank-aan-gouden-invaller-de-ketelaere~1566819483069/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 20 October 2020, De Ketelaere scored the game-winning goal in the 93rd minute to defeat [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit St. Petersburg]] 2–1 in the group stage of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=585853 |title=Club Brugge stun wasteful Zenit with late winner. |website=ESPN |date=20 October 2020 |access-date=20 October 2020 |archive-date=16 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210916024442/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=585853 |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== AC Milan ===
[[File:Charles De Ketelaere 2022 Salzburg vs AC Milan 2022-09-06.jpg|thumb|left|200px|De Ketelaere with [[AC Milan]] in 2022.]]

On 2 August 2022, De Ketelaere joined [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]] on a contract until 30 June 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Charles De Ketelaere joins AC Milan: official statement |url=http://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2022-08-02/official-statement-charles-de-ketelaere |access-date=2 August 2022 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref> Signed for a fee reported to be in the range of €35 million, De Ketelaere however failed to fulfill the initial expectations of the ''Rossoneri'', scoring no goals throughout the entire season and making only nine league starts.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://footballtoday.com/2023/07/19/ac-milan-bust-de-ketelaere-determined-to-redeem-himself/ |publisher=Football Today |date=19 July 2023 |accessdate=16 August 2023 |title=AC Milan flop De Ketelaere determined to redeem himself}}</ref>

=== Atalanta ===
On 16 August 2023, [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] formally confirmed the signing of De Ketelaere from AC Milan on a loan move with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Atalanta BC |date=16 August 2023 |accessdate=16 August 2023 |url=https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/charles-de-ketelaere-is-an-atalanta-player/ |title=CHARLES DE KETELAERE IS AN ATALANTA PLAYER!}}</ref> On 20 August 2023, De Ketelaere came off the bench during Atalanta's Serie A match against [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]], striking the crossbar before sealing his debut Serie A goal with a precise header.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-20 |title=De Ketelaere scores less than 40 minutes into his Atalanta debut |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/watch-de-ketelaere-scores-less-than-40-minutes-into-his-atalanta-debut-38071595 |access-date=2023-09-22 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> The match ended 2–0 in Atalanta's favour.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-20 |title=De Ketelaere and Zortea seal victory over Sassuolo – Atalanta |url=https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/de-ketelaere-and-zortea-seal-0-2-victory-over-sassuolo/ |access-date=2023-09-22 |website=Atalanta BC |language=en-US}}</ref> On 21 September, De Ketelaere marked his presence by netting his first goal in a [[UEFA Europa League]] [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League group stage|group stage]] match against [[Raków Częstochowa]], contributing to Atalanta's 2–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-21 |title=Atalanta seal 2-0 victory over Raków in Europa League opener |url=https://www.atalanta.it/en/news/uel-atalanta-2-0-rakow-czestochowa-in-europa-league-opener/ |access-date=2023-09-22 |website=Atalanta BC |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-21 |title=Atalanta-Rakow 2-0: gol di De Ketelaere ed Ederson, Gasperini torna in Europa con una vittoria |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/coppe/2023/09/21/news/atalanta_rakow_gol_risultato_de_ketelaere-415348373/ |access-date=2023-09-22 |website=[[la Repubblica]] |language=it}}</ref> De Ketelaere scored 14 goals and provided 11 assists in all competitions during his first season at Atalanta; the club made his move permanent on 15 June 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/atalanta-purchase-de-ketelaere-milan/ |title=Official: Atalanta purchase De Ketelaere from Milan |work=Football Italia |date=15 June 2024 |last=Heyes |first=Apollo |access-date=15 June 2024}}</ref> Later that year, on 26 November, he scored a brace and provided a hat-trick of assists in a 6–1 away victory over [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.atalanta.it/news/young-boys-knocked-for-six-in-bern-and-another-ucl-win |title=Young Boys "knocked for six" in Bern and another UCL win! |publisher=Atalanta BC |date=26 November 2024 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Charles_De_Ketelaere_Nations_League_2021_Italy.jpg|thumb|De Ketelaere warming up for the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals|2021 Nations League]] game against Italy]]

In November 2020, De Ketelaere debuted for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian senior squad]] as a substitute in a loss to [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] for the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=L'équipe nationale, "un rêve qui se réalise" pour Charles De Ketelaere|trans-title=The national team, "a dream come true" for Charles De Ketelaere|url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/diablesrouges/2020/11/09/lequipe-nationale-un-reve-qui-se-realise-pour-charles-de-ketelaere-EBVDZ7ITFBDY7GC2AODIVUBPNU/|website=DH Les Sports|date=9 November 2020|access-date=11 July 2024|language=fr}}</ref> On 10 October 2021, he scored his first international goal in the third place playoff match loss to [[Italy national football team|Italy]] for the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League]], 2–1.<ref name="auto"/> In a [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] match against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], De Ketelaere came on as a substitute [[Michy Batshuayi]] in the 75th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/633814/morocco-belgium |title=Belgium 0–2 Morocco |publisher=ESPN |date=27 November 2022 }}</ref>

